<div class="enlarge_html">
    <div class="image_data">
        <p class="caption">National Institutes of Health Director Dr. Francis Collins speak during a news conference in 2017.</p>
        <span class="credit" aria-label="Image credit">
            
            Matt Rourke/AP
            
        </span>
    </div>
</div>
   </div>
   <p>In an bid to help speed up the development of potential treatment options and a vaccine for COVID-19, the National Institutes of Health on Friday announced <a href="https://www.nih.gov/news-events/news-releases/nih-launch-public-private-partnership-speed-covid-19-vaccine-treatment-options">a new public-private research partnership</a>. </p>   <p>The new initiative will be spearheaded by the NIH but also include the Food and Drug Administration, other parts of the federal government and a list of 16 companies that includes some of the biggest players in the pharmaceutical industry. Among the companies participating in the effort are Pfizer, Johnson & Johnson and Merck.</p>   <p>"We need to have all hands on deck from every sector to speed up the process of identifying those treatments that are going to work and to get the vaccines also developed, tested, to make sure they're safe and effective in the maximum possible speed," said Dr. Francis Collins, director of the NIH, in an interview with NPR's <em>All Things Considered. </em></p>   <p>The announcement comes after President Trump and public health officials on Thursday unveiled new <a href="https://www.npr.org/2020/04/16/836489480/read-white-house-guidelines-to-states-for-reopening">guidelines for states to begin reopening the country</a>. Health experts say that in order to safely do that, there needs to be more testing, contact tracing and better drugs to treat COVID-19. Ultimately, for things to truly return to normal, an effective vaccine is needed. </p>   <div id="res837497380" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col ">
            <div class="bucket img">
                  <a id="featuredStackSquareImage834555288" href="https://www.npr.org/sections/health-shots/2020/04/16/834555288/whats-it-going-to-take-to-end-the-shutdown-5-keys-to-containing-coronavirus"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/sections\/health-shots\/2020\/04\/16\/834555288\/whats-it-going-to-take-to-end-the-shutdown-5-keys-to-containing-coronavirus"}' ><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2020/04/14/gettyimages-1209799047_sq-66bfbfb2a7cb10ca45053ddf635ca630d38134ed-s100-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2020/04/14/gettyimages-1209799047_sq-66bfbfb2a7cb10ca45053ddf635ca630d38134ed-s100.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="What's It Going To Take To End The Shutdown? 5 Keys To Containing Coronavirus" /></a>         <div class="bucketblock">
                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/health-shots/">Shots - Health News </a></h3>
            <h3><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/health-shots/2020/04/16/834555288/whats-it-going-to-take-to-end-the-shutdown-5-keys-to-containing-coronavirus"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/sections\/health-shots\/2020\/04\/16\/834555288\/whats-it-going-to-take-to-end-the-shutdown-5-keys-to-containing-coronavirus"}' >What's It Going To Take To End The Shutdown? 5 Keys To Containing Coronavirus</a></h3>
         </div>
         
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKETBLOCK" -->
      </div>
      
<!-- END CLASS="BUCKET IMG" -->
   </div>
   
<!-- END ID="RES837497380" CLASS="BUCKETWRAP INTERNALLINK INSETTWOCOLUMN INSET2COL " -->
   <p>Collins said there are already two vaccines in phase one trials, and behind that, a series of more than 40 other vaccines being developed as well. But he cautioned that the public should expect failures along the way. </p>   <p>"Somewhere in there may be a winner, even if most of them are losers," he said. </p>   <div id="res837491440" class="bucketwrap internallink insettwocolumn inset2col ">
            <div class="bucket img">
                  <a id="featuredStackSquareImage834160187" href="https://www.npr.org/sections/coronavirus-live-updates/2020/04/14/834160187/coronavirus-vaccine-two-pharmaceutical-giants-collaborating-to-develop-one"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/sections\/coronavirus-live-updates\/2020\/04\/14\/834160187\/coronavirus-vaccine-two-pharmaceutical-giants-collaborating-to-develop-one"}' ><img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2020/04/14/gettyimages-1209599222_sq-689b31116138db87d3a8bd37a07a4525292db3ea-s100-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2020/04/14/gettyimages-1209599222_sq-689b31116138db87d3a8bd37a07a4525292db3ea-s100.jpg" class="img lazyOnLoad"  alt="Coronavirus Vaccine? Two Pharmaceutical Giants Collaborating To Develop One" /></a>         <div class="bucketblock">
                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/coronavirus-live-updates/">Coronavirus Live Updates </a></h3>
            <h3><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/coronavirus-live-updates/2020/04/14/834160187/coronavirus-vaccine-two-pharmaceutical-giants-collaborating-to-develop-one"  data-metrics='{"category":"Story to Story","action":"Click Internal Link","label":"https:\/\/www.npr.org\/sections\/coronavirus-live-updates\/2020\/04\/14\/834160187\/coronavirus-vaccine-two-pharmaceutical-giants-collaborating-to-develop-one"}' >Coronavirus Vaccine? Two Pharmaceutical Giants Collaborating To Develop One</a></h3>
